  "prompt": "Can you check your WhatsApp from another phone?",
  "response": "Yes, you can check your WhatsApp from another phone by linking your WhatsApp account to that device. WhatsApp allows you to use the same account on **one phone and up to four additional devices** simultaneously, such as another phone, tablet, or computer. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### **Using WhatsApp on Another Phone**\n1. **Install WhatsApp**: Download and install WhatsApp on the second phone.\n2. **Log In**: Open WhatsApp and verify your phone number. You\u2019ll receive a verification code via SMS or call.\n3. **Transfer Chats (Optional)**: If you want to transfer your chat history, you\u2019ll need to back up your chats from your original phone and restore them on the second phone.\n\n### **Using WhatsApp on Multiple Devices (Companion Mode)**\nWhatsApp allows you to link up to four additional devices to your account without needing your primary phone to be online all the time. Here\u2019s how:\n1. **Open WhatsApp on Primary Phone**: Go to **Settings > Linked Devices**.\n2. **Link a Device**: Tap **Link a Device** and scan the QR code displayed on the second phone or device.\n3. **Use WhatsApp**: Once linked, you can use WhatsApp on the second device independently.\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- Your primary phone must remain active and connected to the internet to link new devices, but it doesn\u2019t need to stay online once the devices are linked.\n- If you log in to WhatsApp on another phone using the same number, your account on the original phone will be logged out unless you use the companion mode mentioned above.\n- Ensure you have a stable internet connection on both devices.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
